{"number":1,"state":"open","dependency":{"package":{"ecosystem":"npm","name":"minimist"},"manifest_path":"package-lock.json","scope":"runtime","relationship":"direct"},"security_advisory":{"ghsa_id":"GHSA-vh95-rmgr-6w4m","cve_id":"CVE-2020-7598","summary":"Prototype Pollution in minimist","description":"Affected versions of `minimist` are vulnerable to prototype pollution. Arguments are not properly sanitized, allowing an attacker to modify the prototype of `Object`, causing the addition or modification of an existing property that will exist on all objects.  \nParsing the argument `--__proto__.y=Polluted` adds a `y` property with value `Polluted` to all objects. The argument `--__proto__=Polluted` raises and uncaught error and crashes the application.  \nThis is exploitable if attackers have control over the arguments being passed to `minimist`.\n\n\n## Recommendation\n\nUpgrade to versions 0.2.1, 1.2.3 or later.","severity":"medium","identifiers":[{"value":"GHSA-vh95-rmgr-6w4m","type":"GHSA"},{"value":"CVE-2020-7598","type":"CVE"}],"references":[{"url":"https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2020-7598"},{"url":"https://snyk.io/vuln/SNYK-JS-MINIMIST-559764"},{"url":"http://lists.opensuse.org/opensuse-security-announce/2020-06/msg00024.html"},{"url":"https://www.npmjs.com/advisories/1179"},{"url":"https://github.com/minimistjs/minimist/commit/10bd4cdf49d9686d48214be9d579a9cdfda37c68"},{"url":"https://github.com/minimistjs/minimist/commit/38a4d1caead72ef99e824bb420a2528eec03d9ab"},{"url":"https://github.com/minimistjs/minimist/commit/4cf1354839cb972e38496d35e12f806eea92c11f#diff-a1e0ee62c91705696ddb71aa30ad4f95"},{"url":"https://github.com/minimistjs/minimist/commit/63e7ed05aa4b1889ec2f3b196426db4500cbda94"},{"url":"https://github.com/advisories/GHSA-vh95-rmgr-6w4m"}],"published_at":"2020-04-03T21:48:32Z","updated_at":"2024-02-13T20:00:55Z","withdrawn_at":null,"vulnerabilities":[{"package":{"ecosystem":"npm","name":"minimist"},"severity":"medium","vulnerable_version_ra